==English==

===Pronunciation===
*tīd'əl wāv, /ˈtaɪdəl weɪv/, /<tt>"taId@l weIv</tt>/

===Noun===
'''[[tidal]] [[wave]]''' (tidal waves)

# A crest of ocean water resulting from tidal forces.
#''(misnomer):'' A large ocean wave, particularly one that comes suddenly and causes great damage; a [[tsunami]]. <!-- Don't need to redefine tsunami here -->
#: ''The last '''tidal wave''' here killed twenty and left thousands homeless.''
# A sudden and powerful surge.
#: ''I was overcome by a '''tidal wave''' of emotions.''

====Usage note====
Recent practice recommends that ''tsunami'' replacewhen the wave is caused by a sudden geological event since such waves are generally not caused by tidal forces.  This reserves the term ''tidal wave'' for those caused by the tidal effects of the sun and moon.  This appears particularly prevalent in scientific circles, where ''tidal wave'' and ''tsunami'' are given distinct technical definitions.

